6710 /// Tests whether the type is categorized as a fundamental type.
6711 ///
6712 /// \returns True for types specified in C++0x [basic.fundamental].
6713 inline bool Type::isFundamentalType() const {
6714  return isVoidType() ||
6715  isNullPtrType() ||
6716  // FIXME: It's really annoying that we don't have an
6717  // 'isArithmeticType()' which agrees with the standard definition.
6718  (isArithmeticType() && !isEnumeralType());
6719 }
6720 
6721 /// Tests whether the type is categorized as a compound type.
6722 ///
6723 /// \returns True for types specified in C++0x [basic.compound].
6724 inline bool Type::isCompoundType() const {
6725  // C++0x [basic.compound]p1:
6726  // Compound types can be constructed in the following ways:
6727  // -- arrays of objects of a given type [...];
6728  return isArrayType() ||
6729  // -- functions, which have parameters of given types [...];
6730  isFunctionType() ||
6731  // -- pointers to void or objects or functions [...];
6732  isPointerType() ||
6733  // -- references to objects or functions of a given type. [...]
6734  isReferenceType() ||
6735  // -- classes containing a sequence of objects of various types, [...];
6736  isRecordType() ||
6737  // -- unions, which are classes capable of containing objects of different
6738  // types at different times;
6739  isUnionType() ||
6740  // -- enumerations, which comprise a set of named constant values. [...];
6741  isEnumeralType() ||
6742  // -- pointers to non-static class members, [...].
6743  isMemberPointerType();
6744 }

7086 bool IsEnumDeclComplete(EnumDecl *);

7089 inline bool Type::isIntegerType() const {
7090  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7091  return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::Bool &&
7092  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
7093  if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType)) {
7094  // Incomplete enum types are not treated as integer types.
7095  // FIXME: In C++, enum types are never integer types.
7096  return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl()) &&
7097  !IsEnumDeclScoped(ET->getDecl());
7098  }
7099  return isBitIntType();
7100 }
7101 
7102 inline bool Type::isFixedPointType() const {
7103  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
7104  return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortAccum &&
7105  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatULongFract;
7106  }
7107  return false;
7108 }
7109 
7110 inline bool Type::isFixedPointOrIntegerType() const {
7111  return isFixedPointType() || isIntegerType();
7112 }

7114 inline bool Type::isSaturatedFixedPointType() const {
7115  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
7116  return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortAccum &&
7117  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatULongFract;
7118  }
7119  return false;
7120 }

7122 inline bool Type::isUnsaturatedFixedPointType() const {
7123  return isFixedPointType() && !isSaturatedFixedPointType();
7124 }
7125 
7126 inline bool Type::isSignedFixedPointType() const {
7127  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
7128  return ((BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortAccum &&
7129  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongAccum) ||
7130  (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortFract &&
7131  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongFract) ||
7132  (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortAccum &&
7133  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongAccum) ||
7134  (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortFract &&
7135  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongFract));
7136  }
7137  return false;
7138 }
7139 
7140 inline bool Type::isUnsignedFixedPointType() const {
7141  return isFixedPointType() && !isSignedFixedPointType();
7142 }
7143 
7144 inline bool Type::isScalarType() const {
7145  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7146  return BT->getKind() > BuiltinType::Void &&
7147  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::NullPtr;
7148  if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
7149  // Enums are scalar types, but only if they are defined. Incomplete enums
7150  // are not treated as scalar types.
7151  return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());
7152  return isa<PointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7153  isa<BlockPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7154  isa<MemberPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7155  isa<ComplexType>(CanonicalType) ||
7156  isa<ObjCObjectPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
7157  isBitIntType();
7158 }
7159 
7160 inline bool Type::isIntegralOrEnumerationType() const {
7161  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7162  return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::Bool &&
7163  BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
7164 
7165  // Check for a complete enum type; incomplete enum types are not properly an
7166  // enumeration type in the sense required here.
7167  if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
7168  return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());
7169 
7170  return isBitIntType();
7171 }
7172 
7173 inline bool Type::isBooleanType() const {
7174  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
7175  return BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Bool;
7176  return false;
7177 }

7222  if (type->isAnyPointerType())
7223  return type->getPointeeType().getTypePtr();
7224  else if (type->isArrayType())
7225  return type->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();

7254 
7255 // Helper class template that is used by Type::getAs to ensure that one does
7256 // not try to look through a qualified type to get to an array type.
7257 template <typename T>
7258 using TypeIsArrayType =
7259  std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<T, ArrayType>::value ||
7260  std::is_base_of<ArrayType, T>::value>;
7261 
7262 // Member-template getAs<specific type>'.
7263 template <typename T> const T *Type::getAs() const {
7264  static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
7265  "ArrayType cannot be used with getAs!");
7266 
7267  // If this is directly a T type, return it.
7268  if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
7269  return Ty;
7270 
7271  // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7272  if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
7273  return nullptr;
7274 
7275  // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
7276  // losing all typedef information.
7277  return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7278 }
7279 
7280 template <typename T> const T *Type::getAsAdjusted() const {
7281  static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value, "ArrayType cannot be used with getAsAdjusted!");
7282 
7283  // If this is directly a T type, return it.
7284  if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
7285  return Ty;
7286 
7287  // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7288  if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
7289  return nullptr;
7290 
7291  // Strip off type adjustments that do not modify the underlying nature of the
7292  // type.
7293  const Type *Ty = this;
7294  while (Ty) {
7295  if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Ty))
7296  Ty = A->getModifiedType().getTypePtr();
7297  else if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<BTFTagAttributedType>(Ty))
7298  Ty = A->getWrappedType().getTypePtr();
7299  else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<ElaboratedType>(Ty))
7300  Ty = E->desugar().getTypePtr();
7301  else if (const auto *P = dyn_cast<ParenType>(Ty))
7302  Ty = P->desugar().getTypePtr();
7303  else if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AdjustedType>(Ty))
7304  Ty = A->desugar().getTypePtr();
7305  else if (const auto *M = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Ty))
7306  Ty = M->desugar().getTypePtr();
7307  else
7308  break;
7309  }
7310 
7311  // Just because the canonical type is correct does not mean we can use cast<>,
7312  // since we may not have stripped off all the sugar down to the base type.
7313  return dyn_cast<T>(Ty);
7314 }
7315 
7316 inline const ArrayType *Type::getAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
7317  // If this is directly an array type, return it.
7318  if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this))
7319  return arr;
7320 
7321  // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
7322  if (!isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType))
7323  return nullptr;
7324 
7325  // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
7326  // losing all typedef information.
7327  return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7328 }
7329 
7330 template <typename T> const T *Type::castAs() const {
7331  static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
7332  "ArrayType cannot be used with castAs!");
7333 
7334  if (const auto *ty = dyn_cast<T>(this)) return ty;
7335  assert(isa<T>(CanonicalType));
7336  return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7337 }
7338 
7339 inline const ArrayType *Type::castAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
7340  assert(isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType));
7341  if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this)) return arr;
7342  return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
7343 }
